<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
ITALY. Sicily: Bronte (Catania province), on cankered twig of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" genus="Pistacia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pistacia vera" order="Sapindales" pageId="3" pageNumber="32" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vera">Pistacia vera</taxonomicName>
, June 2010, A. Belisario (holotype: WU 39967; ex-type culture CBS 128196 = ISPaVe1958).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="32">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="32">
